      "content": "Basal insulin's purpose is to cover your body's continuous insulin needs throughout the day and night, not just to manage post-meal spikes. Skipping it entirely could lead to elevated blood sugar overnight if your underlying needs aren't met. Please contact your endocrinologist or diabetes care team immediately for guidance on how to safely adjust your dose for low-intake nights. They can give you specific instructions suited to your health profile.",
